 are sick. D) Cover your cough or sneeze with a tissue, then dispose of the tissue safely.Hand WashA) Wash your hands often with soap and water for at least 20 seconds especially after you coming from public place. B) If soap and water are not readily available, use a hand sanitizer that contains at least 60% alcohol. C) Avoid touching your eyes, nose, and mouth with unwashed hands.Self IsolationA) Stay home for 14 days from the time you left an area with ongoing spread of virus. B) Stay at home if you begin to feel unwell, even with mild symptoms until you recover. C) If you develop fever, cough and difficulty breathing, seek medical advice promptly.Need for Mandatory Registration of Odisha Migrant WorkersOdisha govt. is successful in containing the spread of the highly infectious diseases in the initial stages by making mandatory registration of people who returned from abroad. Now, the same strategy is being adopted for migrants who come from other states within the country also. Meanwhile, the state govt. has also demanded that corona test of migrants should be done at the place where they are stranded during Coronavirus lockdown.Important Social Feeds of Odisha GovernmentA) CM Twitter: twitter.com/naveen_odisha B) CM Facebook: facebook.com/naveen.odishaImportant LinksA) MoHFW: https://www.mohfw.gov.in/ B) HFW Odisha: https://health.odisha.gov.in/ C) WHO: https://www.who.int/ D) Official Website: https://covid19.odisha.gov.in/  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now Source / Reference Link: https://www.newindianexpress.com/states/odisha/2020/apr/25/portal-for-registration-of-migrant-workers-launched-in-odisha-2134995.html, covid19.odisha.gov.in  at  "}